African National Congress President, Cyril Ramaphosa, will virtually address the party’s 109 year celebrations from Luthuli House in Johannesburg on Friday. @MYANC President Cde @CyrilRamaphosa to address #ANC109 celebration on virtual platforms #StayAtHome #Covid_19SA #ProtectYourself #DefendEachOther #LetsDoItTogether #FlattenTheCurve pic.twitter.com/4jcGSgj2vF — African National Congress #ANC109 (@MYANC) January 7, 2021  Ramaphosa will outline the ANC’s plan of action for the year ahead. For the first time since the governing party was unbanned in 1990, there will be no mass rally due to the outbreak of the COVID-19 pandemic. Head of Organising in the ANC, Nomvula Mokonyane, says efforts to deal with the coronavirus, tackling Gender-Based Violence (GBV) and femicide will form basis of the National Executive Committee (NEC) statement to be presented by Ramaphosa. This year’s celebration will honour the second president of the party, Sefako Makgatho. Makgatho was ANC president between 1917 and 1924. ANC briefing on the 109 birthday celebrations:  